In England, in the seven days to 23 February, there were 199,908 new confirmed cases (353.5 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 16 February, there were 258,656 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 23% (58,748 fewer cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 28 February is 16,059,214 (28,398.2 cases per 100,000 population).
